{"article_id":"ynZe3swiAj7UtKZc","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"The judicial battle over the Trump administration ' s efforts","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"to wind down the Deferred Action for Childhood Arrivals","depth":8},{"id":2,"text":"( DACA )","depth":8},{"id":3,"text":"program ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"which protected 690,000 young unauthorized immigrants from deportation ,","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"has just been extended by several months .","depth":4},{"id":6,"text":"On Monday , the Supreme Court rejected a highly unusual request from the Trump administration :","depth":9},{"id":7,"text":"to skip over the second level of the federal court process","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"( the courts of appeals )","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"by having the Supreme Court consider an order","depth":11},{"id":10,"text":"made in January by a California district court judge .","depth":11},{"id":11,"text":"The January order partially reanimated the DACA program ,","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"which the Trump administration began winding down in September 2017","depth":10},{"id":13,"text":"( with the expectation","depth":12},{"id":14,"text":"that work permits","depth":13},{"id":15,"text":"issued under the program","depth":13},{"id":16,"text":"would start expiring in large numbers on March 5 of this year ) .","depth":11},{"id":17,"text":"Immigrants","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"who have work permits under DACA","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"( or whose work permits recently expired )","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"are currently eligible to apply for renewals under the order .","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"The Trump administration is trying to get that order overturned ,","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"so that it doesn ' t have to renew anyone ' s work permits","depth":8},{"id":23,"text":"while the case over the constitutionality","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"of ending DACA","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"works its way through the courts .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"By rejecting the administration ' s request ,","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"the Supreme Court isn ' t saying anything about the merits of the DACA program itself , or about the legal arguments over the Trump administration ' s decision","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"to end it .","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"It ' s just insisting","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that the case proceed the normal way ,","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"with the Ninth Circuit Court of Appeals hearing the administration ' s appeal of the California judge ' s order","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"( and the Second Circuit Court of Appeals on the East Coast hearing an appeal of a similar order","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"issued in February by a New York judge ) .","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"That process is likely to take months","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"- and it ' s extremely unlikely that both appeals courts","depth":12},{"id":36,"text":"( both of which are fairly liberal","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"and have consistently ruled against the Trump administration on immigration issues )","depth":13},{"id":38,"text":"are going to side with the administration .","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"That means","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"that renewals will likely remain open","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"at least until the Supreme Court agrees to take up the cases after the appeals courts rule","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"- which will almost certainly be during the Court ' s next term ,","depth":12},{"id":43,"text":"which starts in October of this year .","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"In theory , by that point , Congress may have passed a bill","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"to provide a longer-term solution for the status of DACA recipients and other unauthorized immigrants","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"who came to the US as children","depth":13},{"id":47,"text":"( including those","depth":14},{"id":48,"text":"who meet the criteria for DACA","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"but didn ' t apply before September 5 , 2017 ;","depth":15},{"id":50,"text":"even under the federal court orders , no one can apply for DACA for the first time ) .","depth":13},{"id":51,"text":"On the other hand , it ' s possible that Congress could point to the now-prolonged court fight as yet another reason","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"it ' s not urgent for them to act .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"The court fight over DACA is keeping the program on life support","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"-","depth":9},{"id":55,"text":"but it won ' t save it for good","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"On September 5 , the Trump administration announced","depth":12},{"id":57,"text":"that it was ending DACA .","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"The administration immediately stopped accepting new applications for two-year deportation protections and work permits .","depth":11},{"id":59,"text":"DACA recipients","depth":13},{"id":60,"text":"whose work permits were set to expire before March 5 , 2018","depth":13},{"id":61,"text":"were given a month","depth":13},{"id":62,"text":"to apply for one last two-year renewal .","depth":13},{"id":63,"text":"And immigrants","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"whose work permits were set to expire after March 5","depth":15},{"id":65,"text":"were given no chance","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"to renew at all -","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"the expiration date on the work permit","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"they held","depth":14},{"id":69,"text":"would mark the last day","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"they were able to work legally ,","depth":16},{"id":71,"text":"and live","depth":17},{"id":72,"text":"without fear ,","depth":17},{"id":73,"text":"in the United States .","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"( Because not everyone","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"who was eligible for renewals","depth":12},{"id":76,"text":"applied in time ,","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"an average of 122 immigrants are losing DACA protections each day right now ;","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"on March 5 , that number is estimated to climb to over 400 a day ,","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"and around August 2018 , it would climb to over 1,000 a day . )","depth":12},{"id":80,"text":"Several different lawsuits got filed over the end of DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"arguing","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"that the Trump administration had acted illegally","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"in winding down the program .","depth":12},{"id":84,"text":"In one of those","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"- filed by the University of California -","depth":13},{"id":86,"text":"federal judge William Alsup ruled in January","depth":12},{"id":87,"text":"that there was evidence","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"to suggest","depth":14},{"id":89,"text":"that the administration had in fact violated the law ,","depth":14},{"id":90,"text":"by not going through a standard deliberative process","depth":13},{"id":91,"text":"or doing enough","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"to consider the costs","depth":15},{"id":93,"text":"of ending DACA .","depth":15},{"id":94,"text":"Therefore ,","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"he said ,","depth":13},{"id":96,"text":"he was going to put the rollback of the program on hold","depth":12},{"id":97,"text":"while he considered the legal questions more fully .","depth":11},{"id":98,"text":"Here ' s the way","depth":11},{"id":99,"text":"the process is supposed to go from there :","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"the Trump administration would appeal the judge ' s ruling to the 9th Circuit Court of Appeals ,","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"then ,","depth":12},{"id":102,"text":"if the 9th Circuit sided with the judge and against the administration","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"( as is likely ,","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"given the 9th Circuit ' s track record ) ,","depth":15},{"id":105,"text":"take that appeal to the Supreme Court .","depth":13},{"id":106,"text":"Here ' s the way","depth":12},{"id":107,"text":"the process actually went :","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"the Trump administration asked the Supreme Court to let them skip the 9th Circuit .","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"The Department of Justice ' s ostensible reason was that the question","depth":16},{"id":110,"text":"of ending DACA","depth":16},{"id":111,"text":"was so important","depth":15},{"id":112,"text":"that it couldn ' t be dragged out","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"( though , weirdly , the Trump administration didn ' t ask the Supreme Court to immediately put a hold on Judge Alsup ' s ruling ) .","depth":12},{"id":114,"text":"It ' s also possible that the administration ' s disdain for the \" liberal 9th Circuit , \"","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"rooted in the meme","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"that the Supreme Court routinely smacks down liberal decisions","depth":16},{"id":117,"text":"made by the West Coast court ,","depth":16},{"id":118,"text":"led it to figure","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"that the Supreme Court might be okay with bending the rules","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"if it meant cutting the 9th Circuit out .","depth":13},{"id":121,"text":"In the meantime , a New York judge issued a similar ruling to Judge Alsup ' s -","depth":12},{"id":122,"text":"meaning","depth":13},{"id":123,"text":"that","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"even if the 9th Circuit were to somehow side with Trump ,","depth":15},{"id":125,"text":"it wouldn ' t change anything about what the administration could do .","depth":15},{"id":126,"text":"The Department of Justice now has two different rulings","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"it has to overturn","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"to get its way","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"- whether in the 2nd and 9th Circuit Courts , or at the Supreme Court level after one of those circuit courts rules .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"But the administration ' s repeated legal setbacks don ' t mean","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"that DACA is going to last .","depth":6},{"id":132,"text":"For one thing , the program is already living in a weird , zombified form .","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"For another thing , the legal arguments against the administration","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"that the judges have relied on","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"haven ' t been about whether it was legal to end DACA at all -","depth":9},{"id":136,"text":"they ' ve been about whether the administration went about it the right way .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"Even in a worst-case scenario for the administration ,","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"in which even the Supreme Court","depth":11},{"id":139,"text":"( which has granted the administration much more leeway on immigration policy than the 2nd and 9th Circuits )","depth":11},{"id":140,"text":"rules","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"that the administration acted too hastily","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"in killing DACA ,","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"it probably wouldn ' t prevent the administration from going through a slower , more deliberative process","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"and achieving the same result .","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"Approximately 122 immigrants each day , since October , have had their DACA-issued work permits expire","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"because they were unable to apply in time for renewals","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"( after the Trump administration suddenly shortened the application window in September ) .","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"That ' ll add up to about 22,000 immigrants by the time","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"we get to March 5 .","depth":8},{"id":150,"text":"Approximately 668,000 immigrants have work permits","depth":8},{"id":151,"text":"issued under DACA","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"that won ' t expire until March 5 or later .","depth":7},{"id":153,"text":"Both of these groups of immigrants","depth":8},{"id":154,"text":"- as well as immigrants","depth":9},{"id":155,"text":"whose DACA expired between September 5 , 2016 , and September 5 , 2017 -","depth":9},{"id":156,"text":"can apply for a two-year renewal","depth":8},{"id":157,"text":"( thanks to the court order","depth":9},{"id":158,"text":"issued in January ) .","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"An unknown number of them have already applied .","depth":6},{"id":160,"text":"USCIS has started approving renewal applications","depth":8},{"id":161,"text":"and sending out two-year work permits to DACA recipients","depth":9},{"id":162,"text":"who applied","depth":10},{"id":163,"text":"after the renewal window opened in January .","depth":10},{"id":164,"text":"But we don ' t know","depth":9},{"id":165,"text":"how many of those applications have been approved ,","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"or how long USCIS is taking","depth":9},{"id":167,"text":"to process applications .","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"Even when DACA was in full swing ,","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"USCIS recommended","depth":9},{"id":170,"text":"that applicants give them 90 to 120 days","depth":10},{"id":171,"text":"to process a renewal application .","depth":10},{"id":172,"text":"So it is likely that some DACA recipients are watching their work permits expire","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"while their renewals wait in the processing queue .","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"Immigrants","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"whose existing DACA permits have expired","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"haven ' t been rounded up en masse by ICE .","depth":8},{"id":177,"text":"However , some have been turned over to ICE agents","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"and put in deportation proceedings .","depth":8},{"id":179,"text":"An average of 425 immigrants are currently set to lose their work permits each day from March 5 to March 31 , in the absence","depth":9},{"id":180,"text":"of USCIS","depth":10},{"id":181,"text":"sending out any renewals .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"That pace will rocket up to over 1,000 a day","depth":9},{"id":183,"text":"starting in August .","depth":9},{"id":184,"text":"But ...","depth":8},{"id":185,"text":"Any immigrant","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"worried about the loss of her work permit","depth":11},{"id":187,"text":"will be able to apply for a two-year renewal ,","depth":10},{"id":188,"text":"at least until the court order","depth":12},{"id":189,"text":"issued in January","depth":12},{"id":190,"text":"is struck down .","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"Some of them have already done so .","depth":10},{"id":192,"text":"Because it ' s not yet clear how long USCIS is taking to process DACA renewals ,","depth":5},{"id":193,"text":"it ' s not clear how much risk DACA recipients run","depth":6},{"id":194,"text":"of losing their existing work permits","depth":7},{"id":195,"text":"while they wait for the new ones to come in .","depth":7},{"id":196,"text":"If USCIS is working quickly","depth":9},{"id":197,"text":"to send out renewed work permits before March 5 ,","depth":9},{"id":198,"text":"it will probably reduce the number of people","depth":10},{"id":199,"text":"losing their work permits each day","depth":10},{"id":200,"text":"by some amount ;","depth":9},{"id":201,"text":"it ' s more likely ,","depth":11},{"id":202,"text":"given processing time ,","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"that the pace","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"of people","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"losing DACA","depth":13},{"id":206,"text":"will stay at its projected pace through April ,","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"and would then slow","depth":10},{"id":208,"text":"as USCIS starts sending new work permits to renewal applicants .","depth":10},{"id":209,"text":"The lion ' s share of DACA recipients will still be safe for several more months .","depth":8},{"id":210,"text":"As many as 622,000 immigrants have work permits","depth":9},{"id":211,"text":"issued under DACA","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"that won ' t expire until August 1 or later .","depth":8},{"id":213,"text":"At this pace , it would take until February 2019 for more than half of DACA recipients to lose their protections","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"- and that pace doesn ' t reflect any of the renewals","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"that could be issued under the court order .","depth":9},{"id":216,"text":"The Trump administration has said clearly","depth":7},{"id":217,"text":"that ICE won ' t actively target people","depth":8},{"id":218,"text":"whose DACA work permits have expired en masse .","depth":8},{"id":219,"text":"But it ' s said just as clearly","depth":7},{"id":220,"text":"that","depth":8},{"id":221,"text":"if ICE agents happen to come across immigrants","depth":10},{"id":222,"text":"who have lost DACA protections ,","depth":10},{"id":223,"text":"they ' re just as vulnerable to arrest or deportation as anyone else .","depth":9},{"id":224,"text":"Hundreds of thousands of immigrants have been in a state of uncertainty and anxiety since September 2017 - and even earlier ,","depth":3},{"id":225,"text":"as DACA recipients wondered what President Trump would do to them .","depth":3},{"id":226,"text":"Congress still has the power","depth":4},{"id":227,"text":"to alleviate that uncertainty .","depth":4},{"id":228,"text":"But","depth":4},{"id":229,"text":"if it couldn ' t do so","depth":6},{"id":230,"text":"without the impetus of a deadline ,","depth":6},{"id":231,"text":"it may feel even less urgency","depth":6},{"id":232,"text":"without one .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":465,"left":456,"right":464,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":456,"left":377,"right":455,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":377,"left":238,"right":376,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":238,"left":237,"right":5,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":237,"left":0,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":236,"left":235,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":235,"left":234,"right":3,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":234,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"restatement","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":376,"left":361,"right":375,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":361,"left":257,"right":360,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity